-- Honda: aiming for more than 10 percent U.S. market share
-- 
-- Fri Apr 27, 2012 6:36am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2012/04/27/us-honda-us-idUSBRE83Q0A420120427

 

 TOKYO  (Reuters) - Honda Motor Co ( 7267.T ) aims to recover a market share of more than 10 percent in the United States as soon possible, Executive Vice President Tetsuo Iwamura said on Friday. 
 The overall U.S. market will likely grow to 14.3 million vehicles this year, up from 13.5 million seen at the end of 2011, Iwamura told a news conference. (This story corrects name and title of speaker in paragraph 1, clarifies paragraph 2 to show 2011 sales figure is a projection) (Reporting by  Chang-Ran Kim , writing by Mayumi Negishi; Editing by  Joseph Radford )